Implemented. The function follows the same pattern as `modem_pipe_notify_closed`: it uses `pipe_set_events` to reset the event mask to `PIPE_EVENT_OPENED_BIT` (clearing any stale state from before the pipe was opened), then invokes the user callback with `MODEM_PIPE_EVENT_OPENED`.


============================================================
=== Diff ===
============================================================
--- subsys/modem/modem_pipe.c
+++ subsys/modem/modem_pipe.c
@@ -190,7 +190,8 @@
 
 void modem_pipe_notify_opened(struct modem_pipe *pipe)
 {
-    /* MASKED - implement this function */
+	pipe_set_events(pipe, PIPE_EVENT_OPENED_BIT);
+	pipe_call_callback(pipe, MODEM_PIPE_EVENT_OPENED);
 }
 
 void modem_pipe_notify_closed(struct modem_pipe *pipe)




